        { "id": "top", "label": "top", "direction": "bidirectional", "dataType": "value", "angle": 270 },
        { "id": "left", "label": "left", "direction": "bidirectional", "dataType": "value", "angle": 180 },
        { "id": "bottom", "label": "bottom", "direction": "bidirectional", "dataType": "value", "angle": 90 },
        { "id": "right", "label": "right", "direction": "bidirectional", "dataType": "value", "angle": 360 }
      ],
      "inputs": [
        { "key": "root", "label": "root", "type": "any" },
        { "key": "top", "label": "top", "type": "value" },
        { "key": "left", "label": "left", "type": "value" },
        { "key": "bottom", "label": "bottom", "type": "value" },
        { "key": "right", "label": "right", "type": "value" }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        { "key": "root", "label": "root", "type": "any" },
        { "key": "top", "label": "top", "type": "value" },
        { "key": "left", "label": "left", "type": "value" },
        { "key": "bottom", "label": "bottom", "type": "value" },
        { "key": "right", "label": "right", "type": "value" }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## What Is Twilite? walkthrough\n\n1. Hook: most AI output disappears into chat history, folders, or screenshots.\n2. Claim: Twilite keeps ideas as persistent graphs with addresses, views, and visible relationships.\n3. Show the product page: one graph can hold product identity, explanation, evidence, and navigation.\n4. Explain the loop: declaration defines intent, ports expose surfaces, portals move between graphs, and authored nodes stay inspectable.\n5. Explain the value: humans and AI can work in the same semantic space instead of rebuilding context from scratch.\n6. Close with action: open the tutorials, bootstrap the LLM, and start one graph that matters to you.\n\nUse the product page as the visual anchor, not generic slides.",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "launch-content-declaration"
        }
      }
    },
