      "data": {
        "markdown": "## First five launch posts\n\n1. **What Is Twilite?**\n   Persistent graphs instead of disposable chat history.\n2. **Why Structure Matters**\n   Relationships are first-class, so meaning does not flatten into documents.\n3. **Bootstrap the LLM**\n   Show how an agent becomes graph-literate through the handshake.\n4. **The Product Page Is A Graph**\n   Use the Twilite product graph as proof that the medium is the message.\n5. **AI Memory Needs Addresses**\n   Explain why durable, navigable graph surfaces beat context reconstructed from scratch.\n\nSequence: hook -> structure -> AI workflow -> product proof -> philosophical close.",
